{
  "name": "Vanilla Pumpkin Protein Cheesecake",
  "description": "Base protein cheesecake (vanilla SF pudding, pumpkin for moisture/body). Launch point for flavor variants. Low-fat / high-protein; pumpkin does the work fat does in a standard cheesecake. Tuned DENSE (Tier 1+2): pumpkin reduced 120->75g + 2 tbsp AP flour for a firmer set (AP because that's what's on hand — its gluten sets denser than cornstarch), baked DRY (no water bath) to a just-set center and chilled overnight — denser at near-zero macro cost (~127 cal/slice, ratio 8.9). Stays lean; if a bake comes out rubbery rather than densely creamy, add a little fat (more cream cheese or an extra yolk).",
  "tags": [
    "base",
    "cheesecake",
    "protein"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 8,
    "unit": "slices"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "s1",
        "order": 1,
        "instructionText": "Cook the pumpkin in a nonstick pan over medium heat, 3-5 min, stirring, until thickened and nutty. Remove and COOL COMPLETELY (hot mix will scramble the eggs)."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s2",
        "order": 2,
        "instructionText": "Blend the cottage cheese completely smooth (immersion blender or food processor) - no visible curd, or the cheesecake turns grainy."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s3",
        "order": 3,
        "instructionText": "Beat the light cream cheese alone until smooth, then add yogurt, blended cottage cheese, protein powder, sweetener, vanilla, lemon, and vanilla pudding mix. Sift/whisk in the AP flour smooth (no lumps) and mix just until combined — don't overwork it. Warm the bowl ~15 sec if it clumps."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s4",
        "order": 4,
        "instructionText": "Add the eggs and egg white and the cooled pumpkin. Mix just until smooth - do NOT overbeat once eggs are in (air = cracks, and we want a dense set anyway)."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s5",
        "order": 5,
        "instructionText": "Pour into a parchment-lined 9-inch pan. Tap on the counter to level and pop bubbles."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s6",
        "order": 6,
        "temperature": 350,
        "instructionText": "Bake at 325-350F for ~40-50 min — NO water bath; a dry bake sets it denser. Pull when the center is just set with only a slight wobble (~155-160F center), not visibly jiggly. It firms further as it cools — do not chase a fully dry center, that is where a lean cheesecake turns rubbery."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s7",
        "order": 7,
        "instructionText": "Cool: oven off and door cracked 10-20 min, then counter to room temp ~1-1.5 hr (max 2 hr out), then fridge at least 4 hr — overnight is best and gives the densest, firmest set. Best the next day."
      }
    ],
